Mamelodi Sundowns have defeated Golden Arrows 3-0 in an Absa Premiership clash at the Loftus Stadium on Wednesday night.In the 59th minute, Pitso Mosimane brought on Mzikayise Mashaba for Anthony Laffor. The home side netted the third goal in the 74th minute through Themba Zwane. Tau s low cross found Zwane in the box who tapped it in, 3-0.This win put Sundowns on 8th spot on the league. Sundowns have 10 points from five games. Things are looking good for the African Champions at the moment following their three successive wins in the league.Sundowns next game will be against Highlands Park at the Loftus Versfeld Stadium on Sunday . Kickoff is at 15:30 .&nbsp;